subSubSection.paragraph:
Food and Feeding.
Diet of the Altai Mole mainly contains earthworms, followed by insect larvae, millipedes and centipedes (Myriapoda), and other invertebrates. Earthworms were found in 85-3-100% of studied stomachs and made up 63-73-6% of prey items. Most abundant insect larvae were cockchafers (
Melolontha
), click beetles (
Elateridae
), weevils (
Curculionidae
), darkling beetles (
Tenebrionidae
), and crane flies (
Tipulidae
). Stomach contents weigh 0-79-3-4 g. Earthworms are paralyzed by mutilation of anterior segments and cached. Caches containing 100-150 cm” of earthworms were found in molehills under snow.
